President Obama has announced the members of the President's Council of Advisors on Science and Technology (PCAST). PCAST is an advisory group of scientists and engineers who will advise the President and Vice President on scientific and technological matters. The council will be co-chaired by John Holdren, Eric Lander, and Harold Varmus. The members of PCAST include experts in climate change science, geriatric medicine, astrophysics, physics, nanotechnology, chemistry, and more. The council will work to strengthen the country's capabilities in science and technology and apply them to national challenges.